# TelusurServer

This project uses [mise](https://mise.jdx.dev/) for environment management and Python for development.

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Install mise

If you don't have mise installed, follow the instructions at [mise.jdx.dev/install](https://mise.jdx.dev/install).

### 2. Set up the environment

Run the following command in your project directory to set up the environment as specified in `mise.toml`:

```
mise install
```

### 3. Install Python dependencies

After setting up the environment, install the required Python libraries:

```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Running the Project

After installing the dependencies, you can run the application as needed (for example):

```
python app.py
```

---

**Note:**

- Make sure to keep your `mise.toml` and `requirements.txt` files up to date with your project's dependencies and environment requirements.
- For more information on using mise, see the [mise documentation](https://mise.jdx.dev/docs/).
